Installation
------------

Put your Cloud Server into Rescue Mode from the Rackspace Cloud control
panel.

First thing we want to do is formatting our root partition and mount it
to /mnt.

1.  mkfs.ext3 /dev/xvdb1
2.  mount /dev/xvdb1 /mnt

Next we need to download the minimal installation CD and mount it some
place.

1.  cd \~
2.  mkdir inst host
3.  wget
    <http://nixos.org/releases/nixos/latest-iso-minimal-x86_64-linux>
4.  modprobe loop
5.  mount -o loop latest-iso-minimal-x86\_64-linux ./inst
6.  unsquashfs inst/nix-store.squashfs '\*' -d host/nix/store

We also need the unsquashfs binary from squashfs-tools. You can install
it by the following commands.

1.  emerge --sync
2.  emerge squashfs-tools

Next, we extract nix-store.squashfs from the installation medium to
yield a NixOS system we can chroot into.

1.  cp /etc/resolve.conf host/nix/etc/
2.  mkdir host/dev host/proc host/sys
3.  for fn in dev proc sys; do mount --bind /\$fn host/fn; done

